pageContext.description: Ornament rather indistinct - more distinct on one face than on the other.
pageContext.patina: Turquoise blue and green - metal showing through.
pageContext.surface: Exceedingly uneven and corroded in deep pits.
pageContext.associations: Labelled: "Axe found near a (human) skeleton in ploughing a field near Southery, Norfolk, belonging to Mr. William Smith, a similar one now in possession of Mr. William Whitehead of Yaxley was found in the same field under the same circumstances some few years since." Geo. Daintree Chatteris Jany 1889
